					<description><![CDATA[<p>World Heart Day is September 29 ROCHESTER, Minn. — You may have heard of the mind-body connection: the broad concept that&nbsp; thoughts and feelings, especially those related to stress, can influence physical health. Mohamad Alkhouli, M.D., an interventional cardiologist at Mayo Clinic in Rochester, Minnesota, is researching the relationship between the brain and the heart. [&amp;#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/the-brain-heart-connection-mayo-clinic-expert-explains-powerful-tie-that-works-both-ways/">The brain-heart connection: Mayo Clinic expert explains powerful tie that works both ways</a> appeared first on <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org">Mayo Clinic News Network</a>.</p>
